      "content": "fair enough. but if the mainstream consensus is that it's just systemic/socioeconomic issues, then why do the raw statistics for certain groups keep showing such high disparities regardless of income? like, if u control for poverty and education, are those gaps still there? i'm just trying to understand if there's something else being missed in the sociology side of things.",
